dc_description_s: This datalayer displays the counties for the islands, based on a ground condition of January 1, 2000. The primary legal divisions of most states are termed ''counties.'' Each county and statistically equivalent entity is assigned a three-digit Federal Information Processing Standards code that is unique within the state. These codes are assigned in alphabetical order of county or county equivalent within each state.
dc_title_s: UA Census Counties, 2000 - Northern Mariana Islands
